Requirements

1. Page Implementation
	•	Recreate the exact page from the Figma design in Preview 3.
	•	Ensure pixel-perfect accuracy:
	•	Layout
	•	Spacing
	•	Typography
	•	Colors
	•	Component alignment

⸻

2. SDUI Config Usage
	•	Implement using the config pattern defined in:
@packages/ui/src/engine/examples/README.md:1-32
	•	Follow SDUI conventions:
	•	Node structure
	•	$ref, $fn, $merge
	•	Action handling (dispatch, service.call)
	•	Proper data binding

⸻

3. Component Usage
	•	Use only components from:
@packages/ui/src/engine/defaults/component-registry.ts:1-20
	•	Ensure correct usage of registered chart components to match Figma visuals.

⸻

4. Layout Behavior
	•	Sidebar and header must be fixed (non-scrolling).
	•	Only the main content area should scroll.
	•	Maintain correct layout hierarchy and responsiveness.

⸻

5. Interactivity & State
	•	Use page.store / initialState for dynamic behavior.
	•	Ensure the UI is:
	•	Interactive
	•	Reactive
	•	State-driven

Include:
	•	Click interactions (buttons, tabs, menu items)
	•	Input handling (forms, filters, search)
	•	Toggle/selection states
	•	Conditional rendering via state
	•	Dynamic updates via actions (dispatch / state mutations)

⸻

6. Responsiveness
	•	UI should adapt across screen sizes while preserving design fidelity.
	•	Maintain spacing and alignment consistency across breakpoints.

⸻

7. Validation
	•	Open and verify in the browser (Preview 3 route).
	•	Ensure:
	•	Visual match with Figma
	•	Charts render correctly
	•	Interactions work as expected
	•	No runtime/rendering issues
	•	Smooth scrolling behavior (only content scrolls)

⸻

Output Expectation
	•	Complete SDUI config
	•	Fully working in Preview 3
	•	Pixel-perfect UI
	•	Dynamic, interactive, and responsive
	•	Proper usage of registry components and state-driven updates
